title: Transcontinental Railroads 1893
name: Transcontinental Railroads 1893
description:
Prepared for the Shaping the West project at the Stanford Spatial History Lab by Toral Patel and Richard White. Developed to show the growth of the transcontinental railroads, as depicted in the visualization "The Expansion of the Western Railroad" found on the Spatial History Project website.

Source: "Map of the Chicago-Milwaukee & St. Paul Ry. and connections," Chicago, Milwaukee, and St. Paul Railway Company, published 1893.

Projected coordinate system name: USA Contiguous Albers Equal Area Conic
Geographic coordinate system name: GCS North American 1983
